    <abstract id="aspace_d49ae5cf6992afe890a87f773a966c39">The Tamiment Library Artwork Collection consists of artworks found in the collection and artworks donated to the Tamiment Library &amp; Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives.  The artworks consist of paintings, drawings, sculptures, and plaques and depict labor and political leaders from the United States and other countries.  The artworks date from 1880 to 2010.</abstract>
    <physloc id="aspace_19c21051bd50f535b8261d58220916b1">Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please request materials at least two business days prior to your research visit to coordinate access.</physloc>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_4d46202104a15c11fcf33efde2c71ecd">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <processinfo id="aspace_3b21accd0d4a06608bcd1adc40e6d76a">
    <head>Processing Information</head>
<p>In August 2017, eight items were retroactively accessioned into this collection.  All items in the collection were prepared to be moved to offsite art storage in September 2017. In March 2018, Accession 2018.033 was added as an accretion.  In August 2019, five plaques were added to the collection and prepared for offsite storage.</p><p>In the winter and spring of 2026, several items at offsite storage were photographed, and digital surrogates of these items were incorporated.</p>  </processinfo>
  <arrangement id="aspace_07c38418c8cd390cc2316b1fb7c4b505">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>This collection has not been arranged by an archivist. The materials are arranged in the order in which they were added to the collection.</p>  </arrangement>
  <bioghist id="aspace_fed938513e987df29fe27a21c6274f7c">
    <head>Historical note</head>
<p>The Tamiment Library Artwork Collection was created in 2016 to track artworks that had been found in the collection and artworks donated to the Tamiment Library &amp; Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives.</p>  </bioghist>
  <accessrestrict id="aspace_8d7e9ce176f0d402b2f007e986faaa99">
    <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
<p>Materials are open without restrictions.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <userestrict id="aspace_0eb367ca781ef93c9be5fffdbabb88dc">
    <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
<p>Because of the assembled nature of this collection, copyright status varies across the collection. Copyright is assumed to be held by the original creator of individual items in the collection; these items are expected to pass into the public domain 120 years after their creation. The Tamiment Library &amp; Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives is not authorized to grant permission to publish or reproduce materials from this collection.</p><p>For further information about use of physical items where access is limited to digital surrogates, please contact the Director of Special Collections.</p>  </userestrict>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_e8a024ac8f7cf18cdb386d55ea589d8f">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>Materials found in collection; there is no documentation concerning the provenance of these materials.</p>  </acqinfo>
  <prefercite id="aspace_abe0a3db93237ba0f4e07a296b726fc3">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>Identification of item, date; Tamiment Library Artwork Collection; GRAPHICS.039; item identifier; Tamiment Library &amp; Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives, New York University.</p>  </prefercite>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_77bbc2052498c3c1619fa77c3f6c8292">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The Tamiment Library Artwork Collection consist of paintings, drawings, sculptures, and plaques and depict labor and political leaders from the United States and other countries.  The artworks date from 1880 to 2010.</p>  </scopecontent>
