f4dc48b"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>The quote on the plaque reads:  After forty-five years having chosen and followed the unpopular course of a Socialist propagandist, I am entirely at peace with myself.  I have nothing to regret, nothing to apologize for, to me the Socialist movement with its enthusiasm and idealism, its comradeship and struggles, its hopes and disappointments, its victories and defeats has been the best that life has had to offer.</p></scopecontent><controlaccess><genreform source="aat">Plaques (flat objects)</genreform></controlaccess></c><c id="aspace_ba792de9a100939ac9e31a74e8d3686f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Plaque presented to Ben Josephson by the Camp Tamiment Board of Directors</unittitle><unitid>cuid15250</unitid><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/2/archival_objects/855877</unitid><physdesc altrender="whole"><extent altrender="materialtype spaceoccupied">1 item</extent><physfacet>one plaque</physfacet></physdesc><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1947/1947">1947</unitdate><container id="aspace_581a7cc3176037b6c917501563a8c2cf" label="Mixed Materials [31142069363516]" type="Item">GRAPHICS.039.cuid15250</container></did><controlaccess><genreform source="aat">Plaques (flat objects)</genreform></controlaccess></c><c id="aspace_ac245593487050dc1ab33d6d8f6c8345" level="item"><did><unittitle>Thomas Germano, <emph render="italic">The Great Postal Strike, 1970</emph></unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/2/archival_objects/1036258</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1995/1995">1995</unitdate><container id="aspace_81f68ae63a17998b64c35951ab467937" label="Mixed Materials [31142062707867]" type="Item">2</container></did><phystech id="aspace_85f4edf82d68252d762f973a3b4c8e7c"><head>Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements</head><p>Acrylic on canvas, 53.5" x 68" x 2"</p></phystech></c></dsc>
